commit.message: * switch-window.el (switch-window--create-label-buffer): make asciiart show beautiful.
* switch-window.el (switch-window--window-substring): use buffer-substring-no-properties
* switch-window.el (switch-window--create-label-buffer): truncate lines.
Fix typo

Detect dedicated buffers in switch-window-then-swap-buffer

A window with a dedicated buffer (aka `window-dedicated-p') cannot
switch its buffer with another one (fail with a message).

With the optional KEEP-FOCUS non-nil, do not move the focus on the
selected window after switching buffers.
Fix typo

Save windows margins before switching buffer

Saving window-margins in switch-window--prompt allows to restore them
after switching buffer (or closing the temporary overlays).  Manually
and programmatically set windows margins will be restored.

Keep windows margins when switching buffer

Switching buffer via set-window-buffer without setting KEEP-MARGINS
will remove the current window's margins during the operation.

Not setting KEEP-MARGINS in switch-window--display-number allows to
reset windows margins before showing temporary overlays. If dimming
out a buffer (aka switch-window-background non-nil) is chosen, then
it is preferable to set KEEP-MARGINS.

Setting KEEP-MARGINS in switch-window-then-swap-buffer will restore
the margins of the two windows after exchanging their own buffers.

Setting KEEP-MARGINS in switch-window--prompt fixes a bug when used
in combination with perfect-margin-mode: the latter mode customized
windows margins may not take effect unless KEEP-MARGINS was set.
